# What NOT to upload to Vercel for deploy.
#
# Most of this overlaps with .gitignore; Vercel falls back to it, but
# being explicit here keeps the upload size predictable and visible
# at the deploy layer. Anything matched here is excluded from the
# `vercel deploy` upload — Vercel's build environment regenerates
# what it needs.

# ── reproducible build artifacts ────────────────────────────
node_modules/
dist/
.vite/
tsconfig.tsbuildinfo

# ── local-only operational state ────────────────────────────
.env
.env.local
.vercel/                  # local link config — Vercel doesn't need this in the upload

# ── 1.3 GB of capture-pipeline scratch ──────────────────────
# Rendered preset videos / thumbs. Already on R2; catalog entries
# point at the public R2 URLs. Local files here exist purely for
# the capture workflow.
public/videos/
public/thumbs/
public/audio/test-signal.webm

# ── upstream sources for the catalog ingest ─────────────────
favorites/
catalog/.ingest-progress.json

# ── editor + OS noise ───────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
*.log
*~
